Product Id: For the January to June period, the beginning inventory is dated January 1 and the ending inventory is dated July 1. For the July to December period, the beginning inventory is dated July 1 and the ending inventory is dated January 1 of the following year. The inventory data for each period cannot be aggregated to make an annual total. The inventory data is a count at a specific point in time.
Inventories can also be found in table 32-10-0130.

CANSIM Id: On March 10, 2020, the following corrections were implemented: A correction was made to the number of cattle slaughtered in Quebec and Ontario for the period of January to June 2018. Corrections were made to number of interprovincial movements and births in Saskatchewan and Alberta for the period of January to June 2019. A correction was made to the number of births in Nova Scotia for the period of July to December 2019.
